# Color Consistency Standards

**CRITICAL:** CentaurOS has **1,108 hardcoded color classes** across 172 files. This rule enforces the migration to semantic tokens.

## Core Principle

**NEVER use hardcoded color values.** Always use semantic tokens from the design system.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Semantic tokens
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">
<p className="text-muted-foreground">
<span className="text-destructive">

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-slate-100 text-slate-900">  // Wrong
<p className="text-slate-600">  // Wrong
<span className="text-red-500">  // Wrong
```

## 1. Text Colors

| Use Case | Token | Example |
|----------|-------|---------|
| **Primary text** | `text-foreground` | Body text, headings |
| **Secondary text** | `text-muted-foreground` | Descriptions, metadata |
| **Brand accent** | `text-accent` or `text-international-orange` | CTAs, highlights |
| **Links** | `text-primary` or `text-electric-blue` | Interactive links |
| **Success** | `text-status-success` | Success messages |
| **Warning** | `text-status-warning` | Warning messages |
| **Error** | `text-destructive` | Error messages |
| **Info** | `text-status-info` | Informational messages |

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<h1 className="text-foreground">Page Title</h1>
<p className="text-muted-foreground">Subtitle text</p>
<span className="text-destructive">Error message</span>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't hardcode slate/gray colors
<h1 className="text-slate-900">Page Title</h1>  // Wrong
<p className="text-slate-600">Subtitle</p>  // Wrong
<span className="text-red-600">Error</span>  // Wrong
```

## 2. Background Colors

| Use Case | Token | Example |
|----------|-------|---------|
| **Page background** | `bg-background` | Main page wrapper |
| **Card background** | `bg-card` | Card components |
| **Secondary surface** | `bg-secondary` | Subtle backgrounds |
| **Muted surface** | `bg-muted` | Inactive/disabled states |
| **Brand accent** | `bg-accent` | Primary CTAs |
| **Success** | `bg-status-success-light` | Success badges, alerts |
| **Warning** | `bg-status-warning-light` | Warning badges, alerts |
| **Error** | `bg-status-error-light` | Error badges, alerts |

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<div className="bg-background">
<Card className="bg-card">
<Badge className="bg-status-success-light text-status-success-dark">

// ❌ WRONG - Don't hardcode backgrounds
<div className="bg-white">  // Use bg-background
<div className="bg-slate-50">  // Use bg-muted or bg-secondary
<Badge className="bg-green-100 text-green-800">  // Use status tokens
```

## 3. Border Colors

| Use Case | Token | Example |
|----------|-------|---------|
| **Default border** | `border` (no color class needed) | Cards, inputs |
| **Input border** | `border-input` | Form inputs |
| **Muted border** | `border-muted` | Subtle dividers |
| **Accent border** | `border-accent` | Highlighted elements |
| **Error border** | `border-destructive` | Invalid inputs |

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<Card className="border">  {/* Uses semantic border token */}
<Input className={cn(hasError && "border-destructive")} />
<div className="border-b border-slate-100" />  {/* Exception: light dividers */}

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use colored borders without reason
<Card className="border-blue-200" />  // Use border
<Card className="border-foundry-200" />  // Use border
<Input className="border-red-500" />  // Use border-destructive
```

**Exception:** Page header dividers can use `border-slate-100` for ultra-light dividers.

## 4. Brand Colors

Use brand colors for CTAs and highlights only:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Primary CTA
<Button className="bg-accent">Get Started</Button>
<Button className="bg-international-orange">Sign Up</Button>

// ✅ CORRECT - Secondary brand accent
<Link className="text-electric-blue hover:text-electric-blue-hover">
  Learn More
</Link>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't overuse brand colors
<div className="bg-international-orange">  {/* Too dominant */}
<p className="text-international-orange">Body text</p>  {/* Use text-foreground */}
```

## 5. Status Colors

**Always use semantic status tokens for status indicators:**

```tsx
import { StatusBadge } from '@/components/ui/status-badge'

// ✅ CORRECT - Use StatusBadge with semantic status
<StatusBadge status="success">Completed</StatusBadge>
<StatusBadge status="warning">Pending</StatusBadge>
<StatusBadge status="error">Failed</StatusBadge>
<StatusBadge status="info">In Progress</StatusBadge>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use Badge with hardcoded colors
<Badge className="bg-green-100 text-green-800">Completed</Badge>  // Wrong
<span className="text-amber-600">Pending</span>  // Wrong
```

**For custom status implementations:**

```tsx
// Use semantic status tokens
import { getStatusColor } from '@/lib/status-colors'

const statusColor = getStatusColor(task.status)
<div className={statusColor.bar} />  // Uses semantic tokens
```

## 6. Role Colors (User Avatars)

**Use UserAvatar component - it handles role colors automatically:**

```tsx
import { UserAvatar } from '@/components/ui/user-avatar'

// ✅ CORRECT - Automatic role-based colors
<UserAvatar name="John Doe" role="Executive" />

// ❌ WRONG - Don't manually color avatars
<Avatar className="bg-blue-100 text-blue-700">  // Wrong
  <AvatarFallback>JD</AvatarFallback>
</Avatar>
```

See `avatar-standard.mdc` for full UserAvatar guidelines.

## 7. Chart Colors

Use semantic chart colors from design system:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Semantic chart colors
<div className="bg-chart-1">  {/* International Orange */}
<div className="bg-chart-2">  {/* Electric Blue */}
<div className="bg-chart-3">  {/* Emerald */}
<div className="bg-chart-4">  {/* Amber */}
<div className="bg-chart-5">  {/* Purple */}
<div className="bg-chart-6">  {/* Pink */}

// For Recharts/charting libraries
import { chartColors } from '@/lib/chart-colors'

<Bar dataKey="value" fill={chartColors[0]} />
```

## 8. Dark Mode Compatibility

**All semantic tokens support dark mode automatically:**

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Automatically adapts to dark mode
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">
<Card className="bg-card border">
<p className="text-muted-foreground">

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors break dark mode
<div className="bg-white text-slate-900">  // Won't invert in dark mode
<div className="dark:bg-slate-900">  // Don't manually handle dark mode
```

## 9. Hover States

Use semantic hover variants:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<Button className="bg-accent hover:bg-accent/90">
<Link className="text-primary hover:underline">

// ❌ WRONG
<Button className="bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700">  // Use accent token
<Link className="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">  // Use primary token
```

## 10. Migration Strategy

To fix hardcoded colors in existing code:

**Text colors:**
- `text-slate-900` → `text-foreground`
- `text-slate-600` → `text-muted-foreground`
- `text-slate-500` → `text-muted-foreground`
- `text-slate-400` → `text-muted-foreground`

**Background colors:**
- `bg-white` → `bg-background`
- `bg-slate-50` → `bg-muted` or `bg-secondary`
- `bg-slate-100` → `bg-muted`

**Status colors:**
- `text-green-600`, `bg-green-100` → Use `StatusBadge` with `status="success"`
- `text-red-600`, `bg-red-100` → Use `StatusBadge` with `status="error"`
- `text-amber-600`, `bg-amber-100` → Use `StatusBadge` with `status="warning"`
- `text-blue-600`, `bg-blue-100` → Use `StatusBadge` with `status="info"`

